§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $z = (x, y) ∈ 𝗖$. ⦉

  ‖ Since $z ∈ 𝗥^2$, we can identify $z$ with the polar
    coordinates of $(x, y)$ in the plane. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬argument❭ of $z ∈ 𝗖$ is $\tan^{-1}(\im{z}/\re{z})$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the argument of $z$ by $\arg z$.
